2026-07-01T13:43:11Z UTC
Encountered: `npm run build` failed with `EPERM: operation not permitted, unlink 'dist/assets/index-*.js'` while emptying the output directory; a stale build artifact in the sandbox's mounted working directory could not be unlinked by any tool (`rm`, `mv`, Python `os.remove`).
Resolution: Confirmed this is a sandbox filesystem quirk, not a code defect, by running `npx vite build --outDir /tmp/mbam-web-dist-check`, which completed successfully with the same source. `tsc --noEmit` (the first step of `npm run build`) had already passed cleanly.
Encountered: `git checkout -- mbam-web/package-lock.json` (reverting an unintended local `npm install` metadata diff) failed with `Unable to create '.git/index.lock': File exists`; the stale `.git/index.lock` and other `.git/*.lock` files from earlier in this session could not be unlinked, blocking all git write operations against the mounted working copy.
Resolution: Cloned the repository into the sandbox's native filesystem (`/tmp/mbam-clean`), copied only the four intentionally changed source files across (excluding the unintended `package-lock.json` diff), and committed/pushed from that clean clone instead. The mounted working copy's local `package-lock.json` diff was left in place, unreverted, for the user to discard whenever the mount's lock files clear.

